2. 

# Partition (Traning Data : Test Data = 7:3)

pacman::p_load("caret")

y      <- UB$Personal.Loan                            # Target
 
set.seed(200)
ind    <- createDataPartition(y, p=0.7, list=T)       # Training Data 70% 
UB.trd <- UB[ind$Resample1,]                          # Traning Data

UB.ted <- UB[-ind$Resample1,]                         # Test Data

detach(package:caret)

3. R Package rpart

Package "rpart". "rpart" CART , CP (Complexity Parameter) . "rpart" Cross Validation CP , defalut 10-fold Cross Validation. .

rpart(formula, data, method, ...)
  • formula : Target Target ~ .
  • data : formula
  • method : Target class, Target anova .

3-1. 

pacman::p_load("rpart",                   # for Decision tree
               "rattle", "rpart.plot")    # for fancyRpartPlot(  ) ) 

set.seed(200)                             # seed  for cross-validation   
rContol      <- rpart.control(xval=15)    # xval : Number of cross validation
UB.trd.rtree <- rpart(Personal.Loan~., data=UB.trd,                 
                      method="class", control = rContol)         

summary(UB.trd.rtree)

3-3. ( )

. rpart cp , xerror cp .

table              <- UB.trd.rtree$cptable             # cp Table

low.error          <- which.min(table[ ,"xerror"])     # table xerror      
cp.best            <- table[low.error, "CP"]           # CP low.error  cp  

UB.trd.prune.rtree <- prune(UB.trd.rtree, cp=cp.best)  # prune(,  CP)
UB.trd.prune.rtree$cptable                             #    cp tableNA

3-4-2. ROC


1) Package pROC

pacman::p_load("pROC")

test.rtree.prob <- predict(UB.trd.prune.rtree, newdata=UB.ted) #  Training Data    Test Data     
test.rtree.prob <- test.rtree.prob[,2]                         # "1"   


ac         <- as.numeric(as.character(UB.ted$Personal.Loan))   #         NArpp        <- as.numeric(test.rtree.prob)                      # "1"   

rtree.roc  <- roc(ac, rpp, plot=T, col="red")                  # roc( ,  ))

auc        <- round(auc(rtree.roc),3)
legend("bottomright", legend=auc, bty="n")

detach(package:pROC)

3) Package ROCR

pacman::p_load("ROCR")

rtree.pred <- prediction(test.rtree.prob, UB.ted$Personal.Loan)    # prediction( ,  )    

rtree.perf <- performance(rtree.pred, "tpr", "fpr")                # performance(, "", "1-")                        
plot(rtree.perf, col="blue")                                       # ROC Curve

perf.auc   <- performance(rtree.pred, "auc")                       # AUC
auc        <- attributes(perf.auc)$y.values
legend("bottomright", legend=auc, bty="n")

4-3.

"C5.0" . 1~100 .

pacman::p_load("progress",                                              # For progress_bar
               "caret")                                                 # For confusionMatrix

pb      <- progress_bar$new(total = 100)                                # for  NAresults <- c()

ac      <- UB.ted$Personal.Loan                                         #  
 
for(i in 1:100){                                                        #   1~100
  
  pb$tick()
  
  set.seed(200)
  tree  <- C5.0(UB.trd[-9], UB.trd$Personal.Loan, trials=i)             #     
  pp.cm <- predict(tree, UB.ted, type="class")                          #  
  
  
  CM <- confusionMatrix(as.factor(pp.cm), as.factor(ac), positive="1")  # confusionMatrix
  
  results[i] <- as.numeric(CM$overall[1])                               # confusionmatrix  NA}

which.max(results);results[which.max(results)]                          #      

[1] 10
[1] 0.9839786
